name: WaroengTT
address: Jalan Tibubiu, Beraban, Kec. Selemadeg Tim., Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82161, Indonesia
review 1: I stumbled upon this place Nyepi eve while biking through town.  It looked like a nice little local joint so I decided to stop for lunch. It was definitely popular with the locals, but had an international flair that would make tourists feel welcome as well.  The atmosphere was wonderful, the food was amazing, and the place was very clean for this far off the beaten path in Bali.  The staff were very friendly and the food was an excellent value!  This little joint was a real charm, I will definitely be back again before I leave!
review 2: Found this perfect little spot for a light meal. We ordered fried chicken with rice and mie ayam. Both were delicious and satisfying. Always appreciate friendly service and clean waroeng. Can't find a better deal in this village! If near by and looking for food, this is the spot to go!
review 3: Good food and awesome friendly owner. You will not regret stopping there for a bite.
review 4:
Great food, nice people and good prices..

A must-go when you are in the area..
